      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COUNTRY GOD (1) wasn't beaten far over 1200m in this grade last time out and stuck on well behind a good winner, beaten just 1L. Riordan remains in the saddle and her claim comes in handy. Getting up in trip now looks a big tick and he can land the knockout blow this time. SO SI GOD (8) finished off strongly in easier company when just missing in a photo finish. Back up to 1400m is no issue, though the draw is a little query. She's shown good ability early in her career however, and she'll be hard to hold out if she runs to form. WHEELY (9) was impressive when running over the top to score his maiden win as favourite at Pinjarra last time out. Should be suited by the slight rise in trip and he can repeat the dose from a good draw. GANGSTER GODDESS (6) wasn't far away after sitting on the speed at Pinjarra most recently and is not to be discounted. GOD'S CROSS (4) is better than he showed last time out and can improve now out to 1400m.",
